The paper deals with the analysis and computation of depth functions for point sets in the plane, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of stratification induced by the Delaunay depth function, which is related to the topological properties of the point set, and thus falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithmic aspect of computing Delaunay depth contours and the running time analysis suggest that the paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper includes some visualization of the stratification and depth contours, which could be relevant to the sub-field of computer graphics (cs.GR).
